TY  - JOUR
TI  - News or Noise? The Missing Link
AU  - Chahrour, Ryan
AU  - Jurado, Kyle
AB  - [The literature on belief-driven business cycles treats news and noise as distinct representations of agents’ beliefs. We prove they are empirically the same. Our result lets us isolate the importance of purely belief-driven fluctuations. Using three prominent estimated models, we show that existing research understates the importance of pure beliefs. We also explain how differences in both economic environment and information structure affect the estimated importance of pure beliefs.]
